    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>30<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Nov/60</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Dr Sir!Your esteemed Letter<lb/> and its <sic>inclosure</sic> I duly recd. &amp;
                the latter<lb/> I herewith return. I had to see <persName>Mr Goldsmith</persName><lb/>
                <persName>Dr Bondy</persName> &amp; others which delayed my reply.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our address left here several weeks<lb/> ago. The one <add>?</add>
                by <persName>Dr Bondi</persName>
                <add>?</add><lb/> much revision &amp; improvement, was numerously<lb/> signed &amp;
                by this time is—no doubt—in<lb/> the hands of the venerable Rabbi. The<lb/> general
                opinion is that under the<lb/> circumstances we cannot with<lb/> propriety sign a
                second address.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As to publishing a second<lb/> Edition of Devotl. Exercises, I am as
                yet<lb/> undecided. But should I make up my<lb/> mind, I will assuredly address
                myself<lb/> to you on the subject.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My thanksgiving discourse yesterday<lb/> has caused some sensation
                &amp; is published<lb/> this morning in several of the dailies</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I send you for insertion in the<lb/> Occident if you think proper—a copy<lb/> of the
                world which has it more<lb/> correctly than the Herald &amp;c. should<lb/> you
                insert it please not to divide<lb/> it. In the text it should be “The<lb/> nations
                thank Thee O God” instead<lb/> of “O Lord” as the papers have it</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Very respectfully yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">M J Raphall Dr</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
